components.name: Wait for L2 Full Load Flag
components.description: Polls the md.dwh_flag table in the PostgreSQL DWH until the 'l1_to_l2_load_successfull' flag for the previous business day is set.
outputs: Sensor release signal to downstream tasks

upstream_policy.description: First task in the pipeline, no upstream dependencies.

components.name: Generate Load Identifier
components.description: Creates a unique load ID for the workflow and pushes it to XCom for downstream tasks.

components.name: Register Workflow Session
components.description: Inserts a new session record into metadata tables using the generated load ID.
outputs: Session registration record in metadata tables

components.name: Wait for Previous Day Workflow Completion
components.description: Uses an ExternalTaskSensor to wait until the 'end' task of the previous day's DAG run completes successfully.
inputs: External DAG WF_MAIN_DATASETS_LOAD_L2_TO_L2 end task status

components.name: Trigger PostgreSQL Session Cleanup
components.description: Triggers the external DAG 'sys_kill_all_session_pg' to terminate lingering PostgreSQL sessions before parallel execution.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after the external task sensor confirms previous day completion.

components.name: Trigger Reporting Data Preparation
components.description: Starts the external DAG 'wf_data_preparation_for_reports' to prepare reporting datasets, using a dedicated pool.

upstream_policy.description: Runs in parallel after session cleanup.

components.name: Trigger Client Segmentation Load
components.description: Triggers the external DAG 'l1_to_l2_p_load_data_ds_client_segmentation_full' to load client segmentation data.

upstream_policy.description: Runs in parallel after session cleanup.

components.name: Send Completion Flag to SAP
components.description: Sends an HTTP POST to the SAP system indicating successful client segmentation load.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after client segmentation DAG trigger completes.

connections.purpose: Send completion flag to SAP via HTTP POST

components.name: Update Workflow Completion Status
components.description: Updates metadata tables to mark the workflow session as successful after both parallel branches finish.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after both parallel branches have completed successfully.

components.name: Send Failure Notification Email
components.description: Sends an email to configured recipients if any upstream task fails.
inputs: Failure signals from any upstream task

upstream_policy.description: Triggered when any upstream task fails.

trigger_dag_id.description: Identifier of the DAG to trigger for session cleanup

wait_for_completion.description: Whether to wait for the triggered DAG to finish

trigger_dag_id.description: Identifier of the DAG to trigger for reporting data preparation

pool.description: Pool name to use for the task

pool_slots.description: Number of slots to consume from the pool

trigger_dag_id.description: Identifier of the DAG to trigger for client segmentation load

trigger_rule.description: Trigger rule for the email task

recipients.description: Email addresses to notify on failure

sources: md.dwh_flag table in PostgreSQL DWH (load flag for L1L2)
SAP system (receives HTTP POST completion flag)
External DAGs producing client segmentation and reporting datasets
sinks: Metadata tables updated with workflow session registration and completion status
